1. Define a class to represent the JSON structure. This class should include properties for all the data that we want to deserialize. We can use the [JsonProperty] attribute to map the property names in the class to the property names in the JSON string. For example:

```csharp
public class MyData {
    [JsonProperty("id")]
    public int Id { get; set; }

    [JsonProperty("name")]
    public string Name { get; set; }

