Scrum Agile methodology can be tailored to enhance the development of a C# project by employing the following strategies:
1. Continuous integration: This involves integrating code changes into a shared repository frequently, which helps to detect and resolve integration issues early on.
2. Pair programming: This involves two developers working together on the same code, which helps to improve code quality and knowledge sharing.
3. Code reviews: This involves reviewing code changes before they are integrated into the main codebase, which helps to identify and fix issues early on.
4. Retrospectives: This involves regular meetings to reflect on the development process and identify areas for improvement.
In addition to improving productivity and code quality, Scrum Agile methodology can bring flexibility and adaptability to a project. This is because it prioritizes responding to change over following a plan, and encourages iterative development and continuous improvement.
The following C# code sample demonstrates how Scrum Agile methodology can be utilized in a software development project:
```
public class Product
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string Name { get; set; }
    public decimal Price { get; set; }
}
public class ProductRepository
{
    private List<Product> products = new List<Product>();
    public void Add(Product product)
    {
        products.Add(product);
    }
    public void Remove(int id)
    {
        products.RemoveAll(p => p.Id == id);
    }
    public List<Product> GetAll()
    {
        return products;
    }
}
public class ProductService
{
    private ProductRepository repository;
    public ProductService(ProductRepository repository)
    {
        this.repository = repository;
    }
    public void AddProduct(Product product)
    {
        repository.Add(product);
    }
    public void RemoveProduct(int id)
    {
        repository.Remove(id);
    }
    public List<Product> GetAllProducts()
    {
        return repository.GetAll();
    }
}
```
In this code sample, we have three classes: Product, ProductRepository, and ProductService. The Product class represents a product with an ID, name, and price. The ProductRepository class is responsible for managing a collection of products and provides methods for adding, removing, and retrieving products. The ProductService class acts as a mediator between the ProductRepository and the rest of the application, providing methods for adding, removing, and retrieving products.
This code sample demonstrates several aspects of Scrum Agile methodology. Firstly, it follows the principle of "working software over comprehensive documentation" by focusing on the implementation of functional code rather than extensive documentation. Secondly, it utilizes the concept of "user stories" by representing a product as an object with specific attributes and behaviors. Finally, it demonstrates the use of "refactoring" by separating the responsibilities of managing products into separate classes for better organization and maintainability.
Overall, Scrum Agile methodology can be a powerful tool for enhancing the development of a C# project by promoting communication, collaboration, and flexibility. By utilizing strategies such as continuous integration, pair programming, code reviews, and retrospectives, teams can improve productivity and code quality while adapting to changing requirements and priorities.

